Class FoodList

java.lang.Object
lab9.FoodList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Food>
public class FoodList extends Object implements Iterable<Food>
Class representing a collection of Food items. Implemented internally as a singly-linked list per lab specifications, it does not implement all standard linked list functionality, solely that necessary for lab specifications. Can be iterated over. Trivial getters not documented.

    • randomMeal

      public Food[] randomMeal(int numFoods)
      Picks foods at random from the list based on the passed param & returns a meal consisting of the chosen foods. Can select duplicate entries. An attempt has been made to uniformly distribute the chances across all Foods in the list, but it may not have resulted in a truly rigorous pattern of randomization. A moe efficient implementation of this might use a min-heap instead of an ArrayList for the random foods.
      Parameters:
      numFoods - the number of Foods to be included in the random meal.
      Returns:
      an array of Foods of size numFoods containing the randomly-selected meal.
